"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-26-outfits-team-gb-worn-olympics-opening-ceremony-21304855\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"TheOlympics Opening Ceremonyis always a big event - whenLondonhosted the games in 2012, around 27 million people across the UK tuned in, alongside a further 900 million from overseas.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 124, \"end\": 126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999458489629007, \"rank\": 0.0005418033694830526, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"TheOlympics Opening Ceremonyis\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 30}, {\"ngram\": \"a big event\", \"from\": 38, \"to\": 49}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 78}, {\"ngram\": \"around 27 million people\", \"from\": 88, \"to\": 112}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ThoughParishas decided to opt out of a stadium show for the first time, instead hosting it along the banks of the River Seine, anticipation is high.\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 299, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ThoughParishas\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 199}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium show\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 236}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 255}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 291}, {\"ngram\": \"anticipation\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But as each country's representatives prepare to step out this evening, we could not help but wonder: could the outfits selected forTeam GBhave been a little more exciting?\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"each country's representatives\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"the outfits\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"GBhave\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 478}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rower Helen Glover and diverTom Daleywere pictured wearing the 'fits outside the British Embassy in Paris earlier this week.\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.512047212218101e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rower Helen Glover\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 527}, {\"ngram\": \"diverTom Daleywere\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'fits\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"the British Embassy\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 605}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Designed by Ben Sherman, they feature cream and navy bomber-style jackets (with extra red on the cuffs and a four-nation floral design on the back) charmingly paired with a knitted vest covered in little Union Jack-style prints.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 647, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Sherman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Sherman\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Sherman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Sherman\"}, {\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acts_of_Union_1800\", \"score\": 0.998267335787421, \"rank\": 0.001279559875681882, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acts_of_Union_1800\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acts_of_Union_1800\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cream\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 678}, {\"ngram\": \"navy bomber-style jackets\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"extra red\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 724}, {\"ngram\": \"the cuffs\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 737}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-nation floral design\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 769}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"a knitted vest\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 820}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's all very tame, leading some Olympics fans to question whether the design might be a little lacklustre.\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some Olympics fans\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 946}, {\"ngram\": \"a little lacklustre\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Really do not like the white shirts with half a Union Flag,' @TrollyDash commented on one of Team GB's TikTok videos.\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 1096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1072, \"end\": 1079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9523612425868827, \"rank\": 0.0500213128300985, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1082, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7376149016955714e-37, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the white shirts\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1014}, {\"ngram\": \"half a Union Flag\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"@TrollyDash\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The jacket is redeemed by the cool design on the back though.'\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The jacket\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"the cool design\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1139}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, Olympic bronze medallist Monica Aksamit added in a video posted to her own account: 'The UK has been getting a lot of hate for this, and I am just not impressed.'\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1198, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monica_Aksamit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Monica Aksamit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monica_Aksamit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monica_Aksamit\"}, {\"begin\": 1262, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999458489629007, \"rank\": 0.0005418033694830526, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a video\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1229}, {\"ngram\": \"her own account\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1255}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1287}, {\"ngram\": \"hate\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1295}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Monica rated the outfit a forgettable five out of 10, describing it as 'bland' and 'not giving much.'\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monica_Geller\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5129125915980005e-12, \"text\": \"Monica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monica_Geller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monica_Geller\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the outfit\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1360}, {\"ngram\": \"'bland\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1414}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, with that view, here's Metro Lifestyle's take on everything Team GB could've worn or taken inspiration from for the Olympic Opening Ceremony instead, from the style of one particular Spice Girl to historical fashion.\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1568, \"end\": 1584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9993657572780932, \"rank\": 0.000634496127819278, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 1627, \"end\": 1637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spice_Girls\", \"score\": 0.9999981345708084, \"rank\": 1.8654324990853663e-06, \"text\": \"Spice Girl\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spice_Girls\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spice_Girls\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that view\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"Metro Lifestyle's take\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1503}, {\"ngram\": \"inspiration\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"the style\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"historical fashion\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A glaringly obvious comparison, Team GB could've taken inspiration fromGeri Halliwell(AKAGinger Spice) and her famous flag dress - because no matter what society says, they are for everyone.\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1694, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9523612425868827, \"rank\": 0.0500213128300985, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"inspiration fromGeri Halliwell(AKAGinger Spice\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1763}, {\"ngram\": \"her famous flag dress\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1790}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1851}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Geri became the poster girl for Cool Britannia when she asked her sister to stitch a Union Jack tea towel onto her black Gucci mini dress because she wanted to 'celebrate being British.'\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 2040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1886, \"end\": 1900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cool_Britannia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cool Britannia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cool_Britannia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cool_Britannia\"}, {\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gucci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.194979268963436e-18, \"text\": \"Gucci\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gucci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gucci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Geri\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1858}, {\"ngram\": \"the poster girl\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"her sister\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"a Union Jack tea towel\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1959}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wearing with red Buffalo boots while performing Who Do You Think You Are at the 1997 Brit Awards, the iconic dress was sold one year later for \\u00a341,320.\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2127, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999999999704414, \"rank\": 2.949964339348155e-11, \"text\": \"Brit Awards\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"red Buffalo boots\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2072}, {\"ngram\": \"the iconic dress\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2156}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How's that for girl power?\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2221, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"girl power\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Beefeater is a classic British look, and refers to the traditional dress worn by the Yeoman Warders (nicknamed 'Beefeaters') who have guarded the Tower of London since the Tudor Era.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2227, \"end\": 2236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yeomen_Warders\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.263579546931539e-31, \"text\": \"Beefeater\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yeomen_Warders\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yeomen_Warders\"}, {\"begin\": 2250, \"end\": 2257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9952419152851706, \"rank\": 0.004593847720284265, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2312, \"end\": 2326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yeomen_Warders\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yeoman Warders\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yeomen_Warders\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yeomen_Warders\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the traditional dress\", \"from\": 2278, \"to\": 2299}, {\"ngram\": \"Beefeaters\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2349}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tower\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"London\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2388}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tudor Era\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2408}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are also personal bodyguards to King Charles (a service they have offered to the reigning monarch since the early 1500s).\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2448, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"score\": 0.9995567338656917, \"rank\": 0.0002673307843598777, \"text\": \"King\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\"}, {\"begin\": 2453, \"end\": 2460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9950776444357242, \"rank\": 0.00494670480026378, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"personal bodyguards\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2444}, {\"ngram\": \"a service\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2471}, {\"ngram\": \"the reigning monarch\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They do not just have one uniform, either: there is one for state dress (comprised of a glitzy red and gold) and one known as the 'undress' outfit (AKA, the one with the classic dark blue hues).\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2733, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one uniform\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2572}, {\"ngram\": \"state dress\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"a glitzy red\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2637}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2646}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'undress' outfit\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2685}, {\"ngram\": \"AKA\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2690}, {\"ngram\": \"the classic dark blue hues\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No doubt, Team GB would have looked dashing with a few references here and there: gold-piped shorts and a sporty nylon ruff, perhaps?\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9523612425868827, \"rank\": 0.0500213128300985, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a few references\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"gold-piped shorts\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"a sporty nylon ruff\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2858}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Pearly Kings and Queens tradition was borne out of working-class London society - and it combines the outlandishness of British fashion with good-hearted charity.\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 3036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2939, \"end\": 2945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999524620773, \"rank\": 4.2811945613821065e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2994, \"end\": 3001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9952419152851706, \"rank\": 0.004593847720284265, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Pearly Kings\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2886}, {\"ngram\": \"Queens tradition\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2907}, {\"ngram\": \"the outlandishness\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2990}, {\"ngram\": \"good-hearted charity\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was started by Victorian street-sweeper Henry Croft, who was the first to decorate his clothes with mother-of-pearl buttons (hence the name Pearly King) to draw attention to himself as he raised money on the streets.\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3056, \"end\": 3065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victorian_fashion\", \"score\": 0.9999992949854215, \"rank\": 7.050148728543932e-07, \"text\": \"Victorian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victorian_fashion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victorian_fashion\"}, {\"begin\": 3081, \"end\": 3092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Croft\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2815602701645538e-15, \"